India Increases Overseas Borrowing Limit for Companies to $750 Million

-- B y   A n u r a g   J o s h i
-- 
2011-09-25T06:47:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/india-increases-overseas-borrowing-limit-for-companies-to-750-million.html
India  raised the amount that
companies are permitted to borrow from overseas under the so-
called automatic route to $750 million in a financial year from
$500 million, according to a statement from the central bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anurag Joshi in Mumbai at 
